====== USPEX INSTALL =====

1) Download USPEX source code
2) Run ./install.sh
3) Set up the environment variables: PATH and USPEXPATH

   For Bash shell system, add lines in ~/.bashrc or ~/.profile or /etc/profile:
     export PATH=$PATH:$HOME/USPEX_install
     export USPEXPATH=$HOME/USPEX_install

   For C shell system, add lines in ~/.cshrc or ~/.profile or /etc/profile:
     setenv PATH "$PATH:$HOME/USPEX-install"
     setenv USPEXPATH "$HOME/USPEX-install"

4) Source your environment variables
5) Run 'USPEX -h' for detailed information

Have fun!
